Significance and relationship :—The Asteraceae are a family particularly rich in endemics in Somalia . Based on Thulin (2006) , 56 or c. 35 % of the c. 160 indigenous species of Asteraceae are endemic to Somalia ; considering only north Somalia , 45 of 120 species or 37.5 % are endemic. The recent addition of a new species for a genus of Asteraceae endemic to the Flora of Somalia confirms this richness (
Baldesi et al. 2020
). An important reason for this high endemism certainly is the wealth of suitable habitats for a family, the members of which are predominantly present in open types of vegetation.
